recommend check-in on the next real step, since more than one door is now open and none is mechanically forced: HAWM1 (build/run the Sala broadcaster client against this real, booted AVD -- both Sala B0/B1 witnesses already GREEN, so the app-layer work is the honest next lap); HAWM2 (a real GrapheneOS build, needs the full AOSP source tree and a much longer build); or continuing the physical-Pixel shopping thread Keaton named earlier this same day, since HAWM0's own GREEN close is a good moment to decide which door matters more before building further on emulation alone.
